Name: North Fld Cond  (Total) '02
Comments:
2002 Total assay. Qatar shares with Iran the largest single
non-associated gas field in the world, the North Field and most of the
production is for LNG. Qatar is now the world's largest producer of
liquefied natural gas (LNG), with a capacity of more than 31 million
metric tons per annum (mmta), and it expects to reach 77.5 mmta of LNG
exports by 2010. By 2010, Qatar will account for one-third of the
world's LNG supply. Discovered in the early 1970s, the Qatari North
Field currently has estimated reserves of more than 900 trillion
standard cubic feet of recoverable gas. The field covers a total 6,000
square kilometres and extends from slightly onshore to continue all the
way north to the three contract areas, i.e. RasGas (RG), Qatargas (QG)
and North Field Alpha (NFA). The reservoir at the North Field is the
Khuff formation. Within the main Khuff gas-bearing reservoir, four
Khuff zones aredefined. Of the four zones, K-4 is the most prolific and
contains approximately 60 per cent of the gas reserves.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  53.4 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   142.5  deg. C.

The Oben field produces light (35 deg API), low sulfur crude oil (0.05
weight percent) that is high in mercury ( 96 ppb). Oben is part of

Delta. The field was discovered in 1972 and came on stream in 1974. The

operated by the Nigerian Petroleum Development Corporation (NPDC) which
holds 24.75 percent interest. Septa Energy holds 30.25 percent and
SEPLAT Petroleum Development, a consortium with two Nigerian companies,
Platform Petroleum and Shebah Petroleum and Maurel and Prom, holds 45
percent interest.

Name: Okono (ITS) Feb 8 '14
Reference: CVX sample sent to ITS Singapore
Comments:
Okono is a light, sweet crude (40.3 degrees API and 0.06 wt percent
Sulfur) produced from the Okpoho and Okono fields located in OLM 119 in
the Niger Delta, approximately 34 miles offshore Nigeria in water depth
ranging from 210 to 250 ft (65 to 75 m). Although the fields were
discovered in the 1980's, Okono did not startup until 2001 and Okphono
until 2003. Output from the fields are exported through the permanently
moored Mystras FPSO (1 million boe storage capacity and 80,000 b/d
treatment capacity) and is offloaded using a shuttle tanker. Together,
Okono and Okphoho contain initial recoverable reserves of 281 million
boe, of which 105 million boe remain (2014). Output averaged 39,000 b/d
in 2014. ENi operates the field and holds 70 percent interest. NNPC
holds the remaining 30 percent interest. Under the terms of the
contract, NNPC will become the operator once 240 million barrels of oil
has been produced, which is expected to occur in 2019.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  24.3 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   136.5  deg. C.

Name: Okono Exp Bld (CVX) '11
Comments:
Okono is a light, sweet crude with an API of 40.5 deg and 0.06 wt
percent Sulfur. It is produced from the Okpoho and Okono fields located
in OLM 119 in the Niger Delta, approximately 34 miles offshore Nigeria
in water depth ranging from 210 to 250 ft (65 to 75 m). Although the
fields were discovered in the 1980's, Okono did not come on line until
2001 and Okphono until 2003. Oil output from the fields are exported
through the permanently moored Mystras FPSO which has a 1 million boe
storage capacity and 80,000 b/d treatment capacity. Due to an attack on
the Mystras FPSO, production was halted from October 2007 to July 2008.
By 2009 output reached 58,000 b/d, close to its 60,000 b/d capacity.
Together, Okono and Okphoho contain an estimated 1.4 billion boe.
Nigerian National Petroleum Co (NNPC), the operator, holds 87.5 percent
interest and ENi holds the remaining 12.5 percent interest.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  25.9 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   136.5  deg. C.

Name: Okwori Exp Bld (Core) '07
Comments:
Core Laboratories (U.K.) Limited have recently performed a crude oil
analysis on one sample referenced as Okwori composite crude  May 2007
for Addax, the operator. The blend is a mix of Okwori and Nda Oil
Fields in the Niger Delta.  this is a medium, sweet crude. The Okwori
oil field was discovered in OPL 90 offshore Nigeria in 1972 and fifty
miles southwest from the oil city of Port Harcourt. Early appraisal
indicated a complex geological structure and fluid distribution with
lateral and vertical compartmentalization of hydrocarbon pools.
Additionhally to the complexity of the substructures, the wells
produced more sand than expected and the topsides was not equipped to
deal with  the sand production.  Sand traps are used to manage sand
production.  Produced crude is stored on FPSO Sendje Berge which Addax
has a contract now until March 2011. The FSPO has as production
capacity of 60 K b/d. Sodium below detection limit Organic Chloride
below detection limit Flash Point below detection limit Vanadium below
detection limit

Comments:

and 1.45 wt. percent sulfur, is owned and operated by Petroleum
Development Oman (PDO), a joint venture between Oman (60 percent),
Royal Dutch Shell (34 percent), Total (4 percent), and Partex (2
percent). The blend comes from 21 mature oil fields located in the
north and central regions of the country, with Yibal being the largest
contributor. Yibal, like most of Oman s oil fields, is in decline. In
2001 crude production for Oman peaked at over 950,000 b/d, but by 2009,
the average crude production declined to 805,000 b/d. PDO has employed
enhanced oil recovery techniques which are expected to boost oil
production to 900,000 b/d. The quality of the crude blend has also been
degrading over the last 20 years with API decreasing from 38 to 31
degrees.

Comments:
The quality of Oman crude is becoming heavier (which may affect the
yield of its lighter products) as a result of additional production
from enhanced oil recovery (EOR) techniques used on its older field
components. Some of the production increase is (and will) come from the
heavy, sour Harweel cluster (Zalzala, Ghafeer, Sakhiya and Dafaq
fields) and the Al Mukhaizna (15 API) and Qarn Alam fields. Oman's
enhanced oil recovery project at Marmul (21.5 API) is expected to come
online in Jun 2009 and yield 10 kBD. Aluminium below detection limit

Name: Oman Exp Bld (ITS) '11
Comments:
Oman Export Blend, a medium gravity sour crude with an API of 31.9 deg
and 1.45 wt. percent sulfur, is owned and operated by Petroleum
Development Oman (PDO), a joint venture between Oman (60 percent),
Royal Dutch Shell (34 percent), Total (4 percent), and Partex (2
percent). The blend comes from 21 mature oil fields located in the
north and central regions of the country, with Yibal being the largest
contributor. Yibal, like most of Oman s oil fields, is in decline. In
2001 crude production for Oman peaked at over 950,000 b/d, but by 2009,
the average crude production declined to 805,000 b/d. PDO has employed
enhanced oil recovery techniques which are expected to boost oil
production to 900,000 b/d. The quality of the crude blend has also been
degrading over the last 20 years with API decreasing from 38 to 31
degrees.

Name: Oriente Hvy Exp (CVX) '06
Comments:
Ecuador contains approximately 2.1 billion barrels of proven oil
reserves. Combined proven and probable reserves are roughly 3.6
billion barrels. Most of the country's reserves contain heavy, sour
crude oil with gravities in the 25o API to 30 API range. The bulk of
current exploration and production activity is focused in the Oriente,
or Ecuador's Amazon basin region. Ecuador's oil has become
increasingly heavy in recent years as new reserves have had higher
gravities than reserves in older, declining fields. Under Ecuador's
constitution, all subsurface resources are property of the state, but
foreign oil companies are allowed to assist in production activities.
Ishpingo, Tiputini, and Panacocha heavy oil (10-15 API) fields in
the northeastern part of the country, constitute Ecuador's largest
known reserves of heavy oil, with more than 710 million barrels of
recoverable reserves, according to Petroecuador.
The 312-mile long
SOTE pipeline connects the oil-rich Oriente region to the Balao export
terminal located near Esmeraldas.
Oriente crudes are becoming
heavier and more viscous as new fields in the area are brought online.
 So a parallel line was built to carry the heavier crude which need
more pumps to handle the viscosity.
this sample is of the heavier grade of crude from the region.

Name: Ormen Lange Cond (Statoil) '08
Comments:
Operator for the development phase: Hydro Operator for the operational
phase: Shell Location: Block 6305/4,5, 7 and 8, 120 kilometers
north-west of the Møre coast, Mid-Norway. Production start: October
2007 Production: Gas and condensate Reservoir:xReservoir: The reservoir
covers an area roughly 40 kilometers long and eight to ten kilometers
wide, around 3,000 meters below the surface of the sea. Sea depth: 800
to 1,100 metres Partners: StatoilHydro 28,9169 per cent Shell 17,0375
per cent Petoro 36,4750 per cent Dong 10,3420 per cent ExxonMobil
7,2286 per cent The development of the Ormen Lange field in the
Norwegian Sea is one of the largest and most demanding industrial
projects ever carried out in Norway. The field commences production on
1 October 2007, and will be able to cover as much as 20 percent of
Britains gas needs, for up to 40 years. The field has been developed
with sea-floor installations at depths of between 800 and 1,100 meters,
combined with an onshore plant at Nyhamna in Aukra municipality in
Norway, for processing and exporting the gas. Not a single installation
will be visible on the surface of the sea above Ormen Lange when the
field comes on stream. All the installations will be at sea depths of
800 to 1,100 meters. Following a gradual increase in production over
the first two to three years, the field will produce 70 million
standard cubic meters (Sm3) of gas per 24-hour period. Deliveries will
probably continue for 30 to 40 years, since recoverable gas reserves
are estimated to amount to a formidable 397 billion standard cubic
meters. Following processing at the onshore facility in Aukra, the gas
will be exported through the 1,200-kilometer long pipeline Langeled, to
the reception center in Easington on the east coast of Britain. The gas
can also be transported via the riser platform on the Sleipner field in
the North Sea to customers on the European continent. Notes: Salt
content 0.43 ppm. Mercury < 1 ppb. Arsenic <  1.5 ppb. BS&W : NIL
MERCURY <1.0 ppb ARSENIC below detection limit

Comments:
Papa Terra is a heavy gravity (16.3 degrees API), low sulfur (0.67 wt
percent), and viscous (10,100 cSt at 20 degrees C) crude oil. It is
also predicted to have high atmospheric residuum yields (74 vol
percent). Papa Terra is a deepwater, heavy oilfield located offshore

are estimated at 380 million boe. Production is expected to start in
July 2013 with an initial production rate of 35,000 b/d and peak
production reaching 135,000 b/d in 2017. The field was developed using
the P-61 Tension-Leg Wellhead Platform (TLWP) and the P-63 FPSO which
has a processing capacity of 140,000 b/d of oil and 35 mmcfd (1 Mcmd)
of gas, and storage for 1.4 million barrels. Petrobras operated the
field and holds 62.5 percent interest. Chevron holds 37.5 percent
interest.
*** The GC Analysis Covers   5.8 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   133.9  deg. C.

Name: Parque Das Conchas (UNK) '11
Comments:
Parque Das Conchas, also known as BC-10, is located offshore Brazil in
the Campos Basin and includes the Abalone, Argonauta, Massa and Ostra
fields. Phase one of the project started on July 2009 with production
coming from the Abalone, Ostra and Argonauta B-West fields. First oil
from Phase 2 of the project was achieved on Oct 2, 2013 from the
Argonauta O-North field. The third and final phase is targeted for 2014
and involves production from the Massa and Argonauta O-South fields.
Parque Das Conchas inital recoverable reserves were estimated at 328
million boe, of which 241 million boe remain. The field currently
produces about 50,000 b/d and about 20-30 percent is from Argonauta.
Parque Das Conchas is a mid-gravity (23.6 degrees ), low sulfur (0.23
wt percent) and acidic (2.64 mg KOH/g) crude oil. Shell operates BC-10
and holds 73 percent interest. ONGC holds the remaining 27 percent
interest.
*** The GC Analysis Covers   2.5 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   138.1  deg. C.

Name: PAS (Shell) May '13
Comments:
Premium Albian Synthetic (PAS) is a synthetic crude produced from
bitumen from Shell's Athabasca Oil Sands Project s (AOSP) two mines,
the Muskeg River Mine and the Jackpine Mine, and upgraded at the
Scotford Upgrader located near Fort Saskatchewan, Alberta. The
synthetic crude oil is produced by using the hydrogen-addition or
hydro-conversion process to add hydrogen to the bitumen to break up the
large hydrocarbon molecules. The process results in a net volume gain
where 103 barrels of synthetic crude oil is produced for every 100
barrels of bitumen processed. The Muskeg River and Jackpine Mines
production capacity is 155,000 b/d and 100,000 b/d, respectively. The
Scotford Upgrader, which has a design capacity of 255,000 b/d, is
operated by Shell Canada (60 percent). Other partners are Chevron
Canada (20 percent) and Marathon Oil Sands LP (20 percent). PAS is a
light gravity (31.9 degrees API) and low sulfur (0.03 wt percent)
synthetic crude oil.
*** The GC Analysis Covers   3.3 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   128.9  deg. C.

Name: Patos Marinza (SGS) '12
Comments:
Patos Marinza is a large, heavy onshore oilfield located east of the
city of Fier in south central Albania. It holds up to 5.7 billion bbls
of oil in place making it Europe's largest onshore oilfield.
Recoverable reserves are estimated at 181 million boe of which, 152
million boe is recoverable. Production started in 1939 and output is
expected to average 22,000 b/d in 2014 and peak at 32,000 b/d in 2020.
Output from the field is sent a rail tie-in at Fier via a 10 km, 9,500
b/d capacity pipeline. About 15,000 b/d of crude is trucked to storage
tanks to the Vlore port operated by La Petrolifera Italo Albanese. A
second pipeline, which will transport 70,000 b/d from Fier to Vlore,
will be completed in 2015. Patos Marinza is a viscous (25,400 cSt at 20
degrees C), heavy gravity (9.3 degrees API), and high sulfur (5 wt
percent) crude. It is predicted to produce a yield of vacuum residuum
(44.6 vol percent) and atmospheric residuum (71.3 vol percent). The
vacuum residuum is also expected to have a high MCRT concentration
(31.9 wt percent). Patos Marinza is owned and operated by Bankers
Petroleum.
*** The GC Analysis Covers   1.0 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   128.6  deg. C.

Name: Pattani Exp Bld (CVX) '11
Comments:
Pattani Blend is a light gravity (38.1 deg API), low sulfur (0.05 wt
percent) crude that contains high levels of mercury ( 996 ppb). The
blend is produced from fields located in the Pattani Basin in the Gulf
of Pattani, offshore Thailand. The blend consists of the output from
the Plamuk, Yala, and Surat fields located in the Unocal 3 Contract
Area. Output from the Platong and Kaphong fields, located in the Unocal
2 Contract Area, also contribute to the blend. The Pattani Blend
started production in 2001. In 2010, production averaged 38,000 b/d.
The entire Unocal 3 Contract Area had recoverable reserves of 186
million boe and the Unocal 2 Contract Area had initial recoverable
reserves of 26 million boe. By the end of 2010, about 102 million boe
and 14 million boe, respectively, remain. Oil produced in both contract
areas are processed at the Thai Oil Development (TOD1) Platong central
processing platform complex (PLCPP) then piped to the 850,000 bbl
capacity Pattani Spirit FSO. Chevron operates both contract areas.
Ownership of the Unocal 3 Contract Area is held by Chevron (71.25
percent), Mitsui Oil Exploration Company (23.75 percent), and 5 percent
PTTEP. Unocal 2 Contract Area ownership is split between Chevron (70
percent) and Mitsui Oil Exploration Company (30 percent).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  15.3 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   132.6  deg. C.

Name: Pattani RCY (ITS) Mar 22 '17
Comments:
Pattani Blend is a light gravity (38.7 degrees API), low sulfur (0.08
wt percent) crude that is known to contain high levels of mercury. The
blend consists of the output of the Plamuk, Yala, and Surat fields
located in the Unocal 3 Contract Area located in the Pattani Basin in
the Gulf of Pattani. Output from the Platong and Kaphong fields located
in the Unocal 2 Contract Area, also in the Pattani Basin, contribute to
the blend. The Pattani Blend started production in 2001. In 2016,
production averaged 62,000 b/d. The entire Unocal 3 Contract Area had
recoverable reserves of 168 million boe oil and the Unocal 2 Contract
Area had initial recoverable reserves of 36 million boe. By the end of
2016, about 27 million boe and 10 million boe, respectively, remain.
Oil produced in both contract areas are processed at the Thai Oil
Development (TOD1) Platong central processing platform complex (PLCPP)
then piped to the 850,000 bbl capacity Pattani Spirit FSO. Chevron
operates both contract areas. Ownership of the Unocal 3 Contract Area
is held by Chevron (71.25 percent), Mitsui Oil Exploration Company
(23.75 percent), and 5 percent PTTEP. Unocal 2 Contract Area ownership
is split between Chevron (70 percent) and Mitsui Oil Exploration
Company (30 percent).

Name: Pazflor (XOM) '15
Comments:
Pazflor crude oil is a medium gravity (24.7 degrees API), low sulfur
(0.40 wt percent), acidic (1.6 mg KOH/g) crude oil. Pazflor is
producedin the eastern portion of Block 17, about 100 miles off the
coast ofAngola in water depths of 600-1200 m. Production comes from the
heavier Hortensia, Perpetua, and Zinia fields (17-22 degrees API) and
thelighter Acacia field (35-38 degrees API). According to Total, the
operator, the Pazflor subsea gathering network is the most complex
system to ever be built in Angola. It is comprised of 180 km of lines
tying in 49 subsea wells, 10,000 metric tons of subsea equipment, and
the world s largest FPSO that measures at 325 m by 62 m, weighs 120,000
 tons, and can store up to 1.9 million boe. Pazflor has initial
recoverable reserves of 621 million boe and remaining recoverable
reserves of 322 million boe (2015). Production started in 2011 and
output averaged 174,000 b/d in 2015. Total owns 40 percent interest in
the field. Other participants are Statoil (23.33 percent), ExxonMobil
(20 percent), and BP (16.67 percent). Sonogal is the concessionaire.

Name: Permian - Holcomb (CAPROCK) Dec
Comments:
The Permian region is an oil producing area the covers over 96,000
square miles in West Texas and southeastern New Mexico and includes the
Midland, Delaware, Central Basin Platform, and Val Verde Basins.
Remaining recoverable reserves at each basin are 23.8 billion boe, 11.9
billion boe, 4.9 billion boe, and 930.5 million boe, respectively.
Production for each basin averaged 645,100 b/d, 404,000 b/d, 294,100
b/d, and 14,700 b/d, respectively, in 2013. There are several liquids
transportation networks that export liquids to markets including the
Basin Pipeline System, Centurion Pipeline System, and the Longhorn
Pipeline. Permian is a light gravity (41.1 degrees -41.4 degrees API),
low sulfur (0.1 wt percent) crude oil.

Name: Pirana Blend (CVX) Jan 23 '15
Comments:
Pirana is located in Block 67 on the Maranon Basin onshore Peru. Block
67 also includes the Paiche and Dorado fields as well as several
exploration prospects that are currently in evaluation phase. Pirana,
the only field currently in production, started up in December 2013 and
is currently producing 7,500 b/d (2015). Paiche and Dorado are expected
go on stream in 2017. Together, the fields are expected to reach a peak
production rate of 60,000 b/d by 2018. Pirana is a heavy, viscous crude
that requires 15-20 percent diluent in order to transport. Pirana Blend
is viscous (911 cSt at 20 degrees C), medium gravity (20.1 degrees API)
and has a contains 2 wt percent sulfur. It is expected to produce a
VRES with high Ni (989 ppm) and MCRT (36.1 wt percent)
concentrations. Parenco, the sole owner and operator of the block,
plans to drill approximately 175 directional wells from 18 platforms as
well as build processing facilities and the install buried pipelines
that will transport crude oil from the jungle to the Bayovar export
terminal on Peru's Pacific coast.

Name: Pt. Arguello OCS  (CVX) '11
Comments:
The Point Arguello facility, located 10 miles off-shore and 40 miles
west of Santa Barbara offshore California, was discovered in the 1980s
and came on line in 1991. It consists of three fields, each of which
has its own platform. The Hermosa platform was installed 1985, the
Hidalgo platform was installed in 1987, and the Harvest platform was
installed in the late 1980s. Crude oil produced from each platform is
transported by sub-sea pipeline to the Gaviota Facility where it is
pipelined to refineries for further processing. Output in 2004 was
9,300 b/d and cumulative production through 1Q 2005 is estimated at 180
million boe. Pt. Arguello crude is heavy and high in sulfur (19.1 deg
API and 4.86 wt percent sulfur). Estimated recoverable reserves in 1995
were 300 million boe. Plains Exploration and Production Co is the
operator and holds 69.3 percent interest. Other partners are Anadarko
Petroleum (8.3 percent), Delta Petroleum (6.1 percent), Devon Energy
(10.3 percent), Koch Oil (4.3 percent) and Oxbow (1.7 percent).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  13.6 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   137.6  deg. C.

Name: Puffin-7 DST (ITS) '06
Comments:
Puffin is located approximately 80 kilometres south west of the
commercial Jabiru and Challis oil fields and approximately 25
kilometres from the Skua oilfield. Initially, the Company intends to
develop the Proved Reserves in the Puffin Field (comprising the
accumulations discovered by the Puffin-2 and Puffin-5 wells) and
explore the Fairfield Prospect, which is located two kilometres from
Puffin-2. Proved (P90) Reserves estimates for the Puffin Field are
10.4MMstb. In overview, the potential in the Permit comprises the
Reserves in the Puffin Field which range from 10.4 MMstb (P90) to 13.1
MMstb (P10), plus the undiscovered Prospective Resources which include
Puffin Area Additions (5.2 MMstb high estimate) and the Fairfield
Prospect (21.6 MMstb high estimate). Samples indicate that the oil from
the Puffin Field is a high quality sweet light crude with a low wax
content and no metal evident. Samples also indicate that the crude oil
from Puffin-2 is approximately 48 0 API and the oil from Puffin-5 is of
a comparable quality. The reservoir fluid has a low gas oil ratio and
low viscosity. With these characteristics, the Directors believe the
oil is easily producible and is of a premium quality by reference to
the APPI Tapis benchmark. MERCAPTAN below detection limit ACID, WHOLE
CRUDE <0.05, value calculated VIS212 value calculated WAX CVX value
calculated IRON <1.00, value calculated SOLVENT POWER value calculated
SOLVENT REQUIREMENT value calculated WATER <500 COPPER below detection
limit
*** The GC Analysis Covers  26.4 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   140.1  deg. C.

Name: PUO-2A (Core) '10
Comments:
The Pagerungan Utara Offshore oil field, also known as PUO, is located
in the Kangean PSC area located offshore Java, Indonesia. The field
started production in January 2011 with an initial production rate of
4,000 b/d. The entire Kangean PSC area, which includes the Pagerungan
field as well as the Terang, Sirasun and Baturgas fields has initial
recoverable reserves of 10.3 million bbl oil, 20 million bbl
condensate, and 1.9 tcf gas, of which 8.4 million bbl oil, 6.1 million
bbl condensate, and 0.79 tcf gas remains (2011). The Kangean PSC is
operated by Kangean Energy Indonesia, a 50:50 joint venture between
JAPEX and Mitsubishi. Kangean Energy Indonesia and Energi Mega Persada
each holds a 50 percent share.
*** The GC Analysis Covers   3.8 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   134.1  deg. C.

Name: PXB PetroChina Blend (UNK) '17
Comments:
PXB (PetroChina Blend) is a synthetic bitumen (SynBit) blend produced
from bitumen from the the Mackay River Commercial Project (MCRP)
located 25 miles NW of Fort Murray and synthetic crude oil diluent
(Pembina Syncrude and Pembina Horizon) delivered via the McKay East
Pipeline. The MCRP, an in-situ oil sands production facility using
SAGD, is operated by Brion Energy, a 100 percent subsidiary of
PetroChina. It holds about 1.7 billion barrels of recoverable bitumen.
MCRP Phase 1, which started in 2017, has a production capacity of
35,000 b/d bitumen. PXB SynBit's production capacity is 70,000 b/d
(50:50 blend of bitumen and synthetic crude). Phase 2 and 3 are
expected to startup in 2021 and 2023, respectively. PXB is an acidic

Name: Pyrenees Exp Bld DST (BHP) '09
Comments:
This is a paper blend prepared by ITS for BHP using data on
preproduction samples of the actual field(s)-- composition and
components unknown to reader. So this is a calculated printout based
on DST samples not a lab assay!  Pyrenees oil field is in license
block WA-12-R in the South Carnarvon basin, Exmouth Sub-basin,
approximately 20 kilometers offshore from North West Cape, Western
Australia  and produce to a FSPO able to process approximately 96,000
barrels of oil a day.. The Pyrenees fields of Crosby, Ravensworth and
Stickle were discovered in WA-12-R in July 2003 and have estimated
recoverable oil reserves of between 80-120 million barrels of oil and
all of these will be included in the export blend as they are brought
onstream.  Ravesnworth also lies in WA-155 and that portion is also
shared by Inpex together with BHP and Apache.  First production is
expected during the first half of the 2010 calendar year. The
estimated economic field life is 25 years.   There is not field called
'Pyrenees'.  This is the name of the project/development of WA-12R and
the name of the FSPO.  The subject sample is a DST sample.  The actual
field of the sample is not identified although appraisal wells were
drilled on each of the fields.  BHP is operator with 71.4% equity.
reported 105 ppm rsh is probably drilling fluids that seem to create a
positive response to the rsh test if not washed-- chemicals in crude
are reactive to this test.  not likely to be sour.
WAX CVX <2.0 wt%
VANADIUM below detection limit
COPPER below detection limit

Name: Qarun (ITS) Nov 27 '14
Comments:
Qarun crude is produced from several fields (WD 19, North Qarun,
Qarun,Sakr, SW Qarun, Wadi El Rayan, North Harun, and Ahram SW) in the
Qarunconcession located in the Western Desert of the Gindi Basin
onshore Egypt. It is a light (36.2 degrees API), low sulfur (0.22 wt
percent)crude oil. Production started in 1974 with an initial output
rate of 500 b/d. Initial recoverable reserves are 96.7 million boe, of
which 0.2 million boe remain (2015). Output peaked in 1999 at 36,400
b/d and has since declined to 900 b/d (2015). Qarun is processed at a
central facility then transported via pipeline to the Dashour pumping
stationwhere it is stored in two 350,000 storage tanks. Once there is
enoughvolume for a bulk shipment, the crude is sent through the SUMED
line tothe Sidi Kerir Terminal for export. Apache Corporation operates
thefield and has a 50 percent equity stake. Dana Petroleum and Sinopec
Group each holds the remaining 25 percent.

Comments:

this is waxy crude from the qarun concession in the eastern Egyptian
desert. In mid-1997 a pipeline connecting Qarun to Dashour was
completed, production to be exported. This report shows many blended
streams.  Some of th fractions exceed the capability of the lab
equipment without causing cracking.  The 2892 was extended to a FBP of
740*F-far too hot for this sort of raw material.  The resid pours were
ignored-they are very close to crude pours and not likely.  Data from

Name: Qatar Land (ITS) Jun '14
Comments:
The Qatar Land grade is produced from the Dukhan oil and gas field
located onshore Qatar in Block 9 about 80 km West of Doha. Dukhan, the
country's oldest and largest field, came onsteam in 1940 and holds
almost all of the onshore reserves. Production averaged 272,000 b/d
(2013) and is mainly from the Khatiyah, Fahahil and Jaleha reservoirs.
Initial recoverable reserves were 5 billion boe, of which 520 million
boe remain (2014). Output from the field is transported via pipeline to
either Messaieed or Doha. Qatar Land is light gravity (39.3 degrees
API), mid-level sulfur (1.3 wt percent) crude oil that is expected to
produce naphtha and jet fractions with high mercaptan concentrations
(greater than 300 ppm). Qatar Petroleum owns and operates the field.

Comments:
Qinhuangdao (QHD) is an offshore field located in the Bohai Bay in
China, approximately 155 miles SE of Beijing. The field consists of two
fields, QHD 32-6 and QHD 33-1. QHD 32-6 began production in 2001 and
holds an estimated 103 million boe. In 2003 QHD 32-6 average production
was 65,000 b/d. The QHD 33-1 oil field came online in 2009 and is
producing 2,000 b/d from two wells. Output from QHD 33-1 is sent via
subsea pipeline to the facilities at QHD 32-6 for processing, storage
and transportation. QHD is a heavy, low sulfur crude oil with an API of
16 deg and sulfur of 0.26 wt percent. CNOOC is the operator of the QHD
33-1 field, with 100 percent equity. CNOOC is also the operator of QHD
32-6, but holds only a 51 percent interest, with Chevron holding the 49
percent balance.

of the Oso field. The crude, from fields, 20 to 40 miles offshore from
Nigeria's South Eastern region, are brought to shore via a seabed

Name: Rabi Bld Onshore (SHELL)  '09
Comments:
Shell's Rabi-Kounga Oil Field 1996 Rabi-Kounga field Presentation
Located onshore Gabon, the Rabi Field was discovered in 1985 and
comprises a reservoir with aerial coverage of some 60 km2, with a 46 m
thick oil rim overlain by a substantial gas cap and underlain by a
charged aquifer. The exploitation permit for the field was granted in
1987 for a period of 20 years ( up to 1.7.2007). Rabi was brought into
production in 1989 and encouraging reservoir performance, coupled with
further appraisal activities in 1991, led to a significant increase in
technical ultimate recovery (TUR). This invo lved an increase in
expectation reserve to 879 Mmbbl. The project to develop these
additional reserves comprised an additional 76 production wells.
Additional reservoir information collected since that date, and the
results from the recently developed Rabi Multi-sector Simulation Model
has resulted in a downward revision of the reserves estimated for
“Phase II” from 879 to 801 MMbbl. The Rabi field produce
*** The GC Analysis Covers   6.0 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   131.9  deg. C.

Name: Ramba Cond (ITS) '10
Comments:
This sample represents a condensate like material from the Ramba
production facility. The Corridor (Ramba) TAC covers a group of mature
producing oil fields located onshore South Sumatra. The fields
originally started producing in 1910 under Shell operatorship. The
current Technical Assistance Contract (TAC) was awarded in 1968. During
the period of the TAC, production rose from an initial rate of 1,000
b/d to a peak of 35,300 b/d in 1987, after the Ramba and Bentayan
fields were brought onstream. Production has steadily declined since
then, despite the use of EOR techniques, and now averages under 4,000
b/d. Key Issues The TAC is due to expire in October 2010, however the
participants are keen to extend the contract for a further 10 years.
During 2008 and the first half of 2009, a Singapore-based logistics
company, RichLand Group Limited, was in talks to acquire a 75% interest
in TAC operator Elnusa Tristar Ramba from Tristar Global.  During 2009,
this company changed its name to Ramba Ene.  Calcium below detection
limit Sodium below detection limit Wax below detection limit
Asphaltenes below detection limit Acid Number below detection limit
Flash Point below detection limit Vanadium below detection limit

Name: Ras Gharib (ORL) Feb 22 '14
Comments:
Ras Gharib is a blend of output from the Issaran and West Gharib fields
located onshore Egypt near the Gulf of Suez. Together the fields hold
84.3 million boe of initial recoverable reserves of which 43.1 million
boe of recoverable reserves remain. Issaran started production in 1987
and currently produces 3,100 b/d. West Gharib started production in
1999 and is currently producing 11,100 b/d. Output from both fields are
sent to the Ras Gharib terminal for sale and export. Egypt's National
Oil Production Co owns and operates the Issaran field and TransGlobe
Energy Corporation owns the West Gharib fields. Ras Gharib is a
mid-gravity crude (24.9 degrees API) with a high sulfur concentration
(2.6 wt percent) and is expected to produce sour naphtha (323 ppm RSH).

Name: Ratawi (CVX) Apr 19 '13
Comments:
Ratawi, also known as Wafra, is a large onshore field located in the
Partitioned Zone (PZ) situated between Kuwait and the Kingdom of Saudi
Arabia. Ratawi is a medium gravity, sour crude oil (23.4 degrees API
and 3.8 wt percent sulfur) that is expected to produce high mercaptan
naphtha (IBP-350 degrees F, 557 ppm RSH). The crude is produced from
the Ratawi reservoirs in the Wafra, South Umm Gudair, South Fuwaris,
and Humma fields. Ratawi's reservoir volume is estimated at 8.1 billion
barrels of oil in place, of which about 5 billion is recoverable and
about 2 billion remains (2010). Ratawi came on stream in 1954 and
produced 118,000 b/d in 2013. The field is owned and operated by a
50:50 joint venture between Saudi Arabia Chevron and Kuwait Gulf Oil
Company.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  11.8 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   134.6  deg. C.

Name: Ratawi Exp Bld(Core) '07
Comments:
FIELDS IN THE SEGREGATION ARE WAFRA, FUWARUIS, AND UMM GUDAIR.  LOAD
PORT IS MINA SAUD. Chevron's assets in the Partitioned Neutral Zone
(PNZ) come from Texaco's acquisition of Getty Oil's interests in the
area including the long-term concession granted by the Kingdom of Saudi
Arabia to Getty Oil in 1949. Production of both Ratawi & Eocene grades
of crude oil were consumed locally until the refining facilities were
destroyed in 1993 during the Gulf War and Ratawi crude had to be
exported. Ratawi is produced from the smaller, deeper Ratawi reservoir
of the Wafra field while Eocene is produced from the larger, shallow
Eocene reservoir which overlays the Ratawi accumulation. Production
from the two fields is divided equally between Kuwait and the Kingdom
of Saudi Arabia.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  12.5 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   142.3  deg. C.

Name: Ratawi Exp Bld(Core) '09
Comments:
2009 Dec sample sent to Core labs for tfa assay on behalf of CVX as
part of the obligation to assay production.  As of mid-2010, cargoes
are running closer to 24.3-24.4*API than this 24.1* sample. Eocene is
produced from the Wafra, South Umm Gudair and South Fuwaris fields in
the Partitioned Neutral Zone (PNZ) situated between Kuwait and the
Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. The current production is 78 thousand barrels
per day. It is exported out of Mina Saud terminal in the
Kuwait-controlled PNZ. CVX has a 50% stake in the resource. Eocene is
also low in nitrogen, low acidity, and low asphaltenes, and has
relatively low metals in the residue. Eocene is a heavy, high sulfur
crude oil, similar in many respects to grades such as the Egyptian
Gisum. It is suitable for asphalt manufacture.

Name: REDWATER PL Mix (CVX) '07
Comments:
The Leduc-Woodbend discovery established the presence in Western Canada
of large subterranean reefs in the Devonian formation capable of
producing economic quantities of oil and gas. Pembina and Redwater
pipeline are interchangable terms.  The sample is a mix of crude
delivered to Edmonton. Just as geologists and the scientific community
were coming to grips with the implications Leduc, Imperial did it again
on Aug. 30, 1948, when an even larger strike was made on Hilton Cook's
farm at Redwater, 60 kilometres northeast of Edmonton. 2007 sample
taken @ Edmonton from the KinderMorgan tank farm. About three quarters
of a mile east of town, Redwater No.1 keeps pumping out oil like it has
for the past 50 years. SILVER below detection limit ARSENIC below
detection limit BERYLLIUM below detection limit CADMIUM below detection
limit CAESIUM below detection limit POTASSIUM below detection limit

producing lighter oil in the north and east of the field and output is
tied back to the 90,000 b/d FPSO Brasil and 180,000 b/d P-52 FPSO.

southwest area of the field and production is tied back to the 180,000
b/d P-54 FPSO. Production in 2012 averaged 251,000 b/d. Modules 3 and 4
are expected to go onstream in 2014. Petrobras owns and operates the
field.

oil from Ross, Blake and Blake Flank fields. The Ross oil field is
situated in the outer Moray Firth on Blocks 13/28a and 13/29a, 60 km
north of the Scottish coast and 30 km to the south-east of the Captain
field. Originally, Ross was designed to be a small and short
development, but its life expectancy was increased when an adjacent
field, Blake, extended Ross's reserves. Once Blake came online, another
field was explored in the area named Blake Flank, which added to the
area's production life. The Ross field spans across three blocks: UKCS
13/28a, 13/28c and 13/29a. The field is roughly 48 miles (77
kilometers) northeast of St. Fergus, UK, and 72 miles (116 kilometers)
northeast of Aberdeen in a water depth of 360 feet (110 meters). This
is a 37.2API Gravity, light, sweet crude typical of North Sea crude of

Name: Rubiales (Ecopetrol) '08
Comments:
Located in the Llanos Basin, 465 km from Bogota, the Rubiales field is
the company's (Petro Rubiales Energy) key asset. The Rubiales field is
the name given to the Rubiales and Piriri producing concessions. The
blocks have a combined area of 569 . Rubiales consists of mostly basal
sands, which produce heavy oil of 12.5 degrees API. We currently have
79 producing wells on the property, of which 25 are vertical and 54
horizontal. The strategic partner for this asset is Ecopetrol, which is
the Colombian state-owned oil company. We (Petro Rubiales Energy) have
a 50 percent working interest with Ecopetrol in the Piriri Block and a
40 percent interest with Ecopetrol in the Rubiales Block. Geology Oil
is produced from the basal sands of the Carbonera Formation. Throughout
the Colombian plains, fluvial depositional systems contain prolific
hydrocarbon reservoirs. The Tertiary deposits of the Llanos Basin in
Colombia correspond to this specific depositional system, which form
where braided-meander rivers prograde into lacustrine or marine basins.
History The Rubiales field was discovered in 1982, but was abandoned
because the economics of producing heavy oil at that time could not
justify the cost of extraction. In July 2002, Meta Petroleum became the
field operator of the Rubiales and Piriri concessions and in that same
year, drilled six wells, achieving production of 940 bbl/d. In 2003
Meta invested in field development and drilled 14 new vertical wells,
allowing it to reach an average production of 3,817 bbl/d.

Name: Sakhalin (SRC) Mar 15 '15
Comments:
Sokol, also known as Sakhalin 1 Area, consists of three offshore
fields, Chayvo, Odoptu, and Arkutun-Dagi, located in the Sea of
Okhotsk, offshore the eastern tip of Russia's Sakhalin Island. Initial
recoverable reserves were 1.592 billion boe, of which 1.152 billion boe
remain (2014). First oil was achieved at the Chayvo field in 2005. The
Odoptu field started up in 2010 and Arkutun-Dagi will go onstream in
2014. Output from Sakhalin is pipelined to the Far East mainland then
sent to either Rosneft's Komsomolsk-na-Amure refinery, or to the port
of De-Kastri on the Russian mainland for export to Asian markets. The
remaining volumes are sent to Komsomolsk-na-Amure and Khabarovsk for
domestic sales. Sakhalin production averaged 127,000 b/d. ExxonMobil
operates the field and holds 30 percent interest. Other partners are
Sakhalin Oil and Gas Development (30 percent), ONGC (20 percent), and
Rosneft (20 percent). Sokol is a light (45.7 degrees API), low sulfur
(0.17 wt percent) crude oil blend.

Sakhalin Blend, which was first offered in Dec 2014, is composed of gas
condensate from Sakhalin 3's Kirinskoye field as well as output from
Sakhalin 1, which includes three offshore fields (Chayvo, Odoptu, and
Arkutun-Dagi) located in the Sea of Okhotsk, offshore the eastern tip
of Sakhalin Island in Eastern Russia. Sakhalin 1 remaining reserves are
 estimated at 1.272 billion barrels of oil and 7.159 tcfs (2015) and
Sakhalin 3 remaining reserves are estimated at 394 million barrels of
condensate and 17.217 tcf gas (2015). The Chayvu and Odoptu began
producing in 2005 and Arkutun-Dagi startup in Jan 2015. Sakhalin 3's
Kirinskoye field started up in 2013. Sakhalin-1 is operated by
ExxonMobil and is owned by the Exxon Neftegas consortium which is
comprised of Exxon Mobil (30 percent), the Japanese consortium Sodeco
(30 percent), India's ONGC Videsh (20 percent) and Rosneft (20
percent). Sakhalin 3 is owned and operated by Gazprom.

Name: San Ardo Fld (CVX) '07
Comments:
The San Ardo oil operations cover approximately seven square miles and
are located 30 miles north of Paso Robles, just east of State Route
101. San Ardo field produces approximately 7,000 barrels of heavy crude
oil per day. Chevron wants to boost production from its southern
Monterey County oil field in a big way and build a 58-mile pipeline to
help carry the crude to its San Francisco Bay refineries. CVX now
produces about 3,600 equity barrels a day from San Ardo-area wells
which now produces about 3,600 barrels a day from San Ardo-area
wells--Chevron now uses trucks to transport its San Ardo crude to the
Bay Area, generating, on average, 22 tanker-truck trips a day. A
proposed pipeline would eliminate trucking and run from the San Ardo
oil field to the Kettleman-Los Medanos pipeline southeast of Coalinga.
The pipeline would be about 11 inches in diameter and would be buried
from 3 to 5 feet underground. That would eliminate potential visual
impacts, Musser said. The crude oil would be heated to reduce its
viscosity to allow it to move through the insulated pipeline. The
pipeline could handle 4,000 to 32,000 barrels per day SILVER below
detection limit CADMIUM below detection limit POTASSIUM below detection
limit LITHIUM below detection limit PHOSPHORUS below detection limit
PALLADIUM below detection limit PLATINUM below detection limit
RUTHENIUM below detection limit ANTIMONY below detection limit TUNGSTEN
below detection limit

Name: Sapele West Exp Bld (CVX) '11
Comments:
The Sapele field is an onshore field located on block OML 41 in the
northwestern part of the Niger Delta. The oil produced in this field is
light (41.7 deg API), low in sulfur (0.09 weight percent) and has high
mercury ( 124 ppb). Discovered in 1969, Sapele had initial recoverable
reserves of 253 million boe and 496 bcf gas. The field went on stream
in 1971 and by the end of 2010 the field had produced 219 million boe
and 175 bcf gas. In 2010, output averaged 2,000 b/d. Crude is sent to
the 60,000 b/d flowstation and gas is sent and processed at a 60 mcf
capacity non-associated gas plant located on OML 41. Crude oil is
transported to the Forcados terminal via the Amukpe-Rapele pipeline and
then blended into the Forcados grade. The field is operated by the
Nigerian Petroleum Development Corporation (NPDC) which holds 24.75
percent interest. Septa Energy holds 30.25 percent and SEPLAT Petroleum
Development, a consortium with two Nigerian companies, Platform
Petroleum and Shebah Petroleum and Maurel and Prom, holds 45 percent
interest.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  33.0 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   137.7  deg. C.

Name: Sapinhoa (INSP) May '12
Comments:
The Sapinhoa (Guara) oil discovery, located in the Santos basin
pre-salt offshore Brazil in Block BM-S-9, is estimated to contain
recoverable volumes of 1 to 2 Bboe. Petrobras, operator, holds 45
percent interest; BG Group holds 30 percent; and Repsol holds the
remaining 25 percent. Discovered in 2008, Guara was drilled by the
Stena DrillMAX drillship to a total depth of 20,134 feet (6,137
meters). Situated in a water depth of 7,024 feet (2,141 meters),
Guara's discovery well, 1-SPS-55, flowed at a rate of 7,200 boepd. Well
tests revealed a very high well productivity index, confirming the well
will be used in the EWT. The consortium performed an EWT on the field
in 2010, then submitted the Declaration of Commerciality on Dec. 30,
2011. ... The Sapinhoa (Guara) oil discovery, located in the Santos
basin pre-salt offshore Brazil in Block BM-S-9, is estimated to contain
recoverable volumes of 1 to 2 Bboe. Petrobras, operator, holds 45
percent interest; BG Group holds 30 percent; and Repsol holds the
remaining 25 percent. Discovered in 2008, Guara was drilled by the
Stena DrillMAX drillship to a total depth of 20,134 feet (6,137
meters). Situated in a water depth of 7,024 feet (2,141 meters),
Guara's discovery well, 1-SPS-55, flowed at a rate of 7,200 boepd. Well
tests revealed a very high well productivity index, confirming the well
will be used in the EWT. The consortium performed an EWT on the field
in 2010, then submitted the Declaration of Commerciality on Dec. 30,
2011. The consortium will commence the first phase of definitive
development in 2013, which should last until 2016. To start the pilot
production test on the field, Petrobras awarded several contracts for
use on Guara. In January 2010, Petrobras and partners signed a letter
of intent with the Schahin/Modec consortium to charter and operate an
FPSO on the Guara field for a 20-year term. The FPSO will be designed
to process 120,000 bopd and 5 MMcm/d. The Guara pilot FPSO will be
capable of receiving up to 10 producers and 10 injectors, including
spare wells, and the first wells will be vertical to enable better
reservoir management.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  11.7 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   140.5  deg. C.

Name: Schiehallion (Statoil) '11
Comments:
The Schiehallion Area is located in the North Atlantic, about 100 miles
west of the Shetlands off the north of the UK on UK blocks 204/20,
204/25a, 204/25b, 205/16 and 205/21b and includes the Schiehallion and
Loyal fields as well as the non-producing Alligin field. The
Schiehallion and Loyal fields had initial recoverable reserves of 685
million and 125 million boe, respectively, and remaining reserves of
366 million and 64 million boe, respectively. Schiehallion came on
stream in July 1998 and Loyal started up shortly after in Oct 1998.
Alligin is a very small field with 9 million recoverable boe. In 2013,
production was shut in and the field's FPSO (Quad 204) was removed from
the location as part of a redevelopment plan. Production is expected to
resume in 2016 when all work is complete and the new FPSO is
commissioned. Prior to the shut-in, the Schiehallion Area was producing
40,000 b/d. BP operates the entire Schiehallion Area. Schiehallion
partners include BP (33.35 percent), Shell (54.9 percent), OMV (5.88
percent), and Statoil (5.88 percent). BP (50 percent) and Shell (50
percent) own the Loyal and Alligin fields.

Comments:
PT Energi Mega Persada Tbk reported that its operating subsidiary, EMP
Kangean, successfully commissioned production facilities and commenced
commercial oil production from the Sepanjan Island Oil Field in the
Kangean PSC, East Java on January 22, 2007 Production was temporarily
stopped in 2007 due to technical problems with the Floating Storage
Offshore Unit. It was replaced with a nw tanker called Concorde with a
storage capacity of 230,000 bbls. The field recommenced production at a
rate of 3,500 bpd from the SED-1A well. The SED-1A well was drilled in
2006 employing under-balanced drilling (UBD) technology to maximize the
productive potential of the Ngimbang carbonate reservoir. Crude from
this well is 32.2 API gravity with a pour point of 115 *F. BP Migas
approved the plan of development for the field in November 2005

Malaysia in Block PM313, about 80 miles from Kuala Terengganu and 50
miles from Dulang. Sepat was discovered in 2003 and came on stream in
January 2012 with an initial production rate of 8,800 b/d. Peak
production of 16,500 b/d is anticipated to be reached in 2013. The
first cargo is expected to load in May 2012. Output from the field is
tied back to the 500,000 boe capacity Sepat FSO. Sepat recoverable
reserves are 30 million boe. Petronas Carigali owns and operates the
field.

Name: Shaikhan (Saybolt) '13
Comments:
Shaikan is a large onshore oil field that covers 283 square miles and
is located in the Kurdistan region in northern Iraq. Recoverable
reserves are estimated at 2.05 billion boe. The field was discovered in
2009, production started in October 2010 via an extended well test with
an average production rate of 4,700 b/d. Commercial production started
in late 2013 with the commissioning of the field s first production
facility, PF-1. Output is expected to increase from 9,000 b/d (2013) to
a peak rate of 150,000 b/d by 2020 as test well facilities are replaced
by processing facilities. Gulf Keystone operates the field and holds 51
percent interest. Other partners are the Kurdistan Regional Government
(32 percent), MOL (13.6 percent), and Texas Keystone (3.4 percent).
Shaikan is a viscous (1560 Cst at 20 degrees C), heavy (15.9 degrees
API), high sulfur (4.9 wt percent) crude that is expected to produce
naphtha and jet fractions with high mercaptan concentrations (1210 ppm
and 801 ppm, respectively) and a yield of vacuum residuum (40 vol
percent) with a high MCRT concentration (34.6 wt percent).

Comments:

China, or sold to Iran. however, its days as an export grade may be
limited in 2010 when the Tuapse refinery expansion is completed since
Siberian Lt is the design raw material for this expansion project. At
Tuapse, about 90 k b/d were available in 2008. Siberian can be
commingled with Urals to improve the quality of Urals Blend and
Siberian Light becomes unavailable. Alternatively, Siberian Light can
be commingled into CPC Blend or exported separately.  Terhe is
considerable variance in quality and from time to time. This is a
relatively low sulfur grade similar to YK  but of better quality than
Sokol, Urals,  and Vityaz.  Margins relative to Brent have narrowed in
2008-2009 as light, low sulfur crude has become available from

Name: Siri Exp Bld (Statoil) '08
Comments:
The Siri field is located in license 6/95 offshore Denmark, about 130
miles west of Esbjerg in the Danish part of the North Sea. Output from
the field is light (38.4 deg API), low sulfur (0.19 wt percent) crude
oil. Siri was discovered in 1995 and started up in 1999. Initial
reserve estimates were at 50 million boe, however with the startup of
satellite fields Nini and Cecilie in 2003, recoverable reserves were
increased to 65 million boe and the life span was extended from 2007 to
2019-2020. In August 2009, the Siri field was shut down due to a leak
caused by cracks found in a subsea structure beneath the Siri platform.
The crack was temporarily repaired and the field was restarted in
January 2010. Production at year-end 2010 was 3,200 b/d. Prior to the
shutdown, production was at 13,500 b/d. Dansk Olie and Naturgas
(DONG),the operator, holds 50 percent interest with joint venture
partner Noreco (50 percent).

Name: Sirtica Exp Bld (LPI) '08
Comments:
sandy desert region that is essentially a northward extension of the
Sahara (desert), north-central Libya; it is the site of one of the
world's largest oil fields. The region fronts the Mediterranean Sea for
about 300 miles (480 km) along the southern part of the Gulf of Sidra
and extends generally southeastward through the Sirte (Surt) Basin. It
is bordered on the west by the northwest-southeast-running volcanic
massif of Al-Haruj al-Aswad (rising to 3,937 feet [1,200 m]). Sirtica
was isolated from the ancient Greek (eastern) and Punic (western)
cultural trends, and as a result it was a refuge for outcasts. About
500 BC an altar was erected in the region to mark the boundary between
the Greek and Punic realms. Sirtica also formed the dividing line
between the Muslim west (the Maghrib) and the Muslim east (the Mashriq)
from the 7th century AD. The bulk of Libya's oil deposits are scattered
throughout the Sirtica region and in the Sirte Basin in particular; the
Sarir oil field is located southeast of the region. The petroleum
reservoirs in the Sirtica are estimated to lie at depths of between 500
and 13,000 feet (150 and 4,000 m) below the surface. Commercial
exploitation began in 1959 at Dahra field. Zaltan, the largest field in
Libya, was discovered the same year and lies about 105 miles (169 km)
south of the Mediterranean port of Mars Al-Burayqah. The crude
extracted in the Sirtica region is light and has a low sulfur content.
The oil is transported northwestward by pipeline to terminals at
As-Sidrah, Ra`s al-Unuf, Mars al-Burayqah, and Az-Zuwaytinah on the
Gulf of Sidra. Besides petroleum extraction, salt is also produced in
large quantities.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  21.3 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   139.9  deg. C.

Name: Snohvit Cond (Statoil) '11
Comments:
Snohvit is a sulfur condensate with an API of 61.3 deg API and 0.02 wt
percent sulfur. Snohvit is a large gas field complex which includes
three fields: Snohvit, Askeladd and Albatross. It is located in the
Norwegian section of the Barents Sea north of the Artic Circle that
holds both condensate, natural gas liquids and natural gas. The field
came on stream in September 2007. Initial recoverable reserves are
estimated at 113 million barrels of condensate. Condensate and natural
gas is produced from 10 wells, which includes six located on the main
Snohvit reservoir, one CO2 injection well, and three on the Albatross
accumulation south of Snohvitthe field. The output is transported
through a 143 km pipeline to the onshore Melkoya LNG plant where the
condensate is separated and the gas is liquefied into LNG. Carbon
dioxide, which is also produced, is separated and sent back to the
field for injection and storage in the Tubasen shale-capped sandstone
formation below the producing zones. Two more wells are planned for
2011 and in 2014-2015, Askeladd will be developed. Snohvit average
condensate production averaged 14,400 in 2010 . In 2008, it was
estimated the field's remaining reservers were at 110 million barrels
condensate, 74.1 million bbl of natural gas liquids, and5.6 trillion
cubic feet of natural gas. StatoilHydro is the operator of the field
and holds 33.53 percent interest. Other joint venture partners are
State Petoro (30 percent), Total (18.4 percent), GDF Suez (12 percent),
Hess (3.26 percent), and RWE Dea (2.81 percent).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  72.7 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   145.2  deg. C.

Name: Sokol (GSC) May 20 '17
Comments:
Sakhalin Blend, also known as SOKOL, is a light (34.6 degrees API), low
sulfur (0.299 wt percent) crude blend. Sakhalin Blend, which was first
offered in Dec 2014, is composed of gas condensate from Sakhalin 3's
Kirinskoye field as well as output from Sakhalin 1, which includes
three offshore fields (Chayvo, Odoptu, and Arkutun-Dagi) located in the
Sea of Okhotsk, offshore the eastern tip of Sakhalin Island in Eastern
Russia. Sakhalin 1 remaining reserves are estimated at 1.14 billion
barrels of oil and 44 million barrels of condensate (2017) and Sakhalin
3 remaining reserves are estimated at 283 million barrels of condensate
(2017). The Chayvu and Odoptu began producing in 2005 and Arkutun-Dagi
startup in Jan 2015. Sakhalin 3's Kirinskoye field started up in 2013.
Sakhalin-1 is operated by ExxonMobil and is owned by the Exxon Neftegas
consortium which is comprised of Exxon Mobil (30 percent), the Japanese
consortium Sodeco (30 percent), India's ONGC Videsh (20 percent) and
Rosneft (20 percent). Sakhalin 3 is owned and operated by Gazprom.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  20.4 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   136.7  deg. C.

Name: Sokol (XOM) Oct 30 '10
Comments:
Sokol, also known as Sakhalin 1 Area, consists of three offshore
fields, Chayvo, Odoptu, and Arkutun-Dagi, located in the Sea of
Okhotsk, offshore the eastern tip of Russia's Sakhalin Island. Initial
recoverable reserves were 1.592 billion boe, of which 1.152 billion boe
remain (2014). First oil was achieved at the Chayvo field in 2005. The
Odoptu field started up in 2010 and Arkutun-Dagi will go onstream in
2014. Output from Sokol is pipelined to Russia s Far East mainland then
sent to either Rosneft's Komsomolsk-na-Amure refinery, or to the port
of De-Kastri on the Russian mainland for export to Asian markets. The
remaining volumes are sent to Komsomolsk-na-Amure and Khabarovsk for
domestic sales. Sakhalin 1 production averaged 127,000 b/d in 2013.
ExxonMobil operates the field and holds 30 percent interest. Other
partners are Sakhalin Oil and Gas Development (30 percent), ONGC (20
percent), and Rosneft (20 percent). Sakhalin 1 is a light (36.4 degrees
API), low sulfur (0.26 wt percent) crude oil that is expected to
produce a vacuum residuum with a high nitrogen concentration (11,800
ppm).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  21.1 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   134.6  deg. C.

Name: Sokol Exp Bld (XOM) '09
Comments:
Sokol, a Russian Falcon was approved by the Sakhalin 1 partners as the
name for Sakhalin 1 crude production.  The Sakhalin 1 Project consists
of three fields Chayvo, Odoptu and Arkutun-Dagi offshore the north east
coast of Sakhalin Island un the Russian Far East.  Together they
contain an estimated 2.3 billion barrels of oil and 17.1 trillion cubic
feet of gas.  Sokol crude is exported from the Sakhalin 1 DeKastri
Terminal. In winter a portion of the Tartar Straits, the body of water
between the Russian mainland and Sakhalin Island is covered with ice.
In order to provide safe, reliable and environmentally sound
transportation, the Sakhalin 1 project acquired a dedicated fleet of
five ice strengthened Aframax size tankers to transport Sokol crude to
the market.  The Sakhalin 1 project also hired two high powered ice
breakers and several other specially designed vessels to support year
round export operations.

Name: SOKOL Fld (SRC) '10
Comments:
The three offshore fields that make up Sakhalin 1 (Chayvo, Odoptu, and
Arkutun-Dagi) are located in the Sea of Okhotsk, offshore the eastern
tip of Sakhalin Island in Eastern Russia. Together they contain an
estimated 2.3 billion barrels of oil and 17.1 trillion cubic feet of
gas. Sakhalin Light, also known as Sokol, is a light, sweet, low
acidity crude with an API of 36.1 deg and less than 0.25 weight percent
sulfur. The Chayvu and Odoptu began producing in 2005 and Arkutun-Dagi,
the third field, is expected to startup in 2014. In 2010, the
production rate was 145,000 b/d, down from its peak of 250,000 b/d in
2007. Sokol crude is exported from the Sakhalin 1 DeKastri Terminal.
Sakhalin Light is operated by ExxonMobil and is owned by the Exxon

Name: Song Doc Exp Bld (CVX) '09
Comments:
Song Doc, a light gravity (38.6 degree API), sweet (0.04 weight percent
sulfur) crude oil, is produced on Block 46/02 in the Malay-Tho Chu
Basin, offshore southern Vietnam. The field was discovered in 2003 and
began producing oil in 2008. Production peaked at 25,000 b/d in 2009,
however output in 2011 has fallen to an average of 6,000 b/d.
Recoverable reserves are estimated at 16 million b/d and by year end
2011, about 4 million boe remain. Song Doc crude is tied back to the
TSJOC Song Doc MODEC MV19 FPSO which has a production capacity of
25,000 b/d and can store up to 360,000 b/d. The field is owned and
operated by the Truong Son Joint Operating Company which is composed of
PetroVietnam (40 percent), Petronas Carigali (30 percent), and Talisman
(30 percent).

Name: Songkhla D (ITS) '12
Comments:
Songkhla D, also known as Bua Ban North A, is an offshore oil field
located off the southeastern coast of Thailand in the G5/43 block. The
field produces a medium gravity (26.9 degrees API), low sulfur (0.16 wt
percent sulfur) crude oil with a high pour point (93 cSt at 20 degrees
C) and high arsenic content (718 ppb). The crude is also expected to
have a high atmospheric residuum yield (79.7 vol percent). Songkhla D
was discovered in March 2011 and began producing a few months later in
Dec 2011. Recoverable reserves are estimated at 25.9 million boe.
Production in 2012 has averaged 6,000 b/d and is expected to peak at
8,500 b/d in 2013. Output from Songkhla D is transported to a leased
FSO that also takes in production from Songkhla E fields. Costal Energy
is the owner and operator of all G5/43 block fields.
*** The GC Analysis Covers   1.2 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   132.7  deg. C.

NIOC owned and operated South Pars is located in the Iranian part of
the Persian Gulf between Iran and Qatar and is a part of the supergiant
North Field that is being developed in 24 phases. South Pars Phases
6/7/8 is a low sulfur condensate (60.1 degrees API, 0.22 wt percent
sulfur) that is expected to produce distillate fractions with high
mercaptan concentrations. Initial reserves are 313 boe LPG and 972
million barrels of condensate of which, 237 million boe of LPG and 728
million barrels of condensate remain (2016). Liquids production, which
started in 2008, averaged 99,000 boe/d (75,000 b/d condensate and
24,000 boe/d LPG) in 2016.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  58.1 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   139.0  deg. C.

Name: St. Malo (CVX) '13
Comments:
St. Malo crude is a light gravity (30.8 degrees API), mid-level sulfur
(1.8 wt percent) crude oil that has a high measured Ca content (299
ppm). The offshore, deepwater oil field is located in the WR 678 block
in the US Gulf of Mexico, in 6,900 ft water depths. Recoverable
reserves are estimated at 383 million barrels of oil and 96 bcf gas.
St. Malo and the nearby Jack field, which holds an additional 230
million boe and 60 bcf gas, will be jointly developed and are expected
to start production in 2014. Output from both fields, as well as
production from nearby fields, will be tied back to a floating
production unit with a production capacity of 177,000 barrels of
oil-equivalent per day. From there, the produced oil will be
transported through the Chevron Pipeline Company operated Jack and St.
Malo (JSM) Oil Export Pipeline (OEP) to the Shell operated Boxer
Platfrom located in Green Canyon block 19 (GC-19). The crude will then
be tied into the Amberjack pipeline system which terminates at
Fourchon, Louisiana. Chevron operates the field and holds 51 percent
interest. Other partners are Petrobras (25 percent), Statoil (21.5
percent) ExxonMobil (1.25 percent) and ENI (1.25 percent).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  14.9 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   135.1  deg. C.

Name: Statfjord Bld (Statoil) '16
Comments:
Statfjord Blend is a light (38.8 degrees API), low sulfur (0.19 wt
percent) crude oil that is produced from the giant offshore Statfjord
oil and gas field in the Tampen area that straddles between the
UK/Norway median line. The Snorre field, also located in the Tampen
Area, contributes to the blend. Stat fjord started up in 1979 and
Snorre started up in 1992. Statfjord Initial reserves were 3.625
billion boe, 270 million barrels LPG, 10 million barrels of condensate
and 2.877 tcf gas. Remaining reserves at Statfjord are 27 million boe,
36 million barrels LPG, 3 million barrels condensate and 258 bcf gas.
Initial reserves for Snorre was 1.686 billion boe, 37 million barrels
LPG and 229 bcf gas and remaining reserves are 373 million boe, 1
million barrels LPG and 9 bcf gas. In 2016, total liquids production at
Statfjord and Snorre averaged 57,000 b/d (23,000 b/d oil, 32,000 b/d
LPG and 3,000 b/d condensate) and 100,000 b/d, respectively. Snorre is
owned by Statoil (operator, 33.32 percent), Norway DFI (30 percent),
Exxon (17.76 percent), Idemitsu (9.6 percent), DEA (8.28 percent), and
Point Resources (1.04 percent). Statfjord is owned by Statoil (51.88
percent, operator), Exxon (25 percent), and Centrica (23.13 percent).

Name: Su Tu Den #2 (ITS) Oct '12
Comments:
Su Tu Den is a blend of crudes from several fields located in the
southeast corner of block 15-1 in the Cuu Long Basin of Vietnam. It is
processed and stored in the Thai Binh-VN FPSO, formerly known as the
Cuulong M/V 9. The three main producing fields, also known as the
Golden Triangle, are Sutu Den (including Sutu Den Northeast), Sutu
Vang, Su Tu Nau and Sutu Trang. Each field holds recoverable reserves
of 250 million boe, 70 million boe, 50 million, and 485 million boe,
respectively. Su Tu Den, the main component, came on line in 2003 and
production for Su Tu Den Northeast began in May 2010. Sutu Vang
initiated in 2008, Sutu Trang is targeted to begin in 2012, and Su Tu
Nau is still under evaluation. Su Tu Den is a waxy, light, low sulfur
crude (37.6 degrees API and 0.06 wt percent Sulfur) with a high crude
pour point (86 degrees F). Production rates in 2011 averaged 83,000
b/d. Output from the Su Tu Den development utilizes the FPSO Cuulong
MV9, which can store up to 1 million boe and process 65,000 b/d. The
fields are operated by the Cuu Long Joint Operating Co., a joint
venture between Petrovietnam (50 percent), ConocoPhillips (23.3
percent), Korea National Oil Corp. (14.2 percent), SK Innovation (9
percent) and Geopetrol (3.5 percent).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  18.5 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   137.8  deg. C.

Name: Su Tu Den Exp Bld (CVX) '10
Comments:
Sutu Den is a blend of crudes from several fields located in the
southeast corner of block 15-1 in the Cuulong Basin of Vietnam. It is
processed and stored in the Thai Binh-VN FPSO, formerly known as the
Cuulong M/V 9. The three main producing fields, also known as the
Golden Triangle, Sutu Den (including Sutu Den Northeast), Sutu Vang,
and Sutu Trang hold an estimated reserve of 600 million boe, 720
million boe, and 120 million boe, respectively. Sutu Den, the main
component, came on line in 2003 and production for Sutu Den Northeast
began in May 2010. Sutu Vang initiated in 2008 and Sutu Trang is
targeted to begin in 2012. Sutu Den is a waxy, light, low sulfur crude
(36 deg API and 0.07 weight percent Sulfur). Production of the Sutu Den
field is in decline because of water pressure issues associated with
fractured basement reservoirs in the Cuu Long Basin, however this is
offset by an increase production of the lighter Sutu Vang (37 deg API)
which is causing an increase in the blend s API. Production rates in
2009 averaged 93,000 b/d and are expected to increase in 2010 and
beyond as Sutu Den Northeast production ramps up and Sutu Trang comes
on line. The fields are operated by the Cuu Long Joint Operating Co., a
joint venture between Petrovietnam (50 percent), ConocoPhillips (23.3
percent), Korea National Oil Corp. (14.2 percent), SK Innovation (9
percent) and Geopetrol (3.5 percent).

Name: Suez Exp Bld (BP) '04
Comments:
Gulf of Suez is a Low Acidity, high Sulphur, heavy Crude Oil with high
Vanadium content, high Nickel content and a low Crude Oil Pour Point.
High Sulphur content could require extended desulphurisation capacity
in many Refineries. The H2S measured at 160  C was <5 ppm Wt. Kerosene
(149-232) Density, Sulphur and Freeze Point fits specification for Jet
A1. Gasoil / Diesel (232-342) low Density, medium Sulphur. Cetane Index
indicates suitability for Gasoil and Diesel production although
Desulphurisation wil l be necessary. Vacuum Gasoil (369-550) medium
Density, high Sulphur. Basic Nitrogen indicates potential FCC feed
although high level of Sulphur may cause SO2 emissions from the FCC to
exceed air pollution limits in some Countries. Dewaxed Oil data indic
ates good Lube potential. Atmospheric Residue (>369) medium Density,
high Sulphur. high Metals content and high Carbon Residue indicate that
product should be processed in a Vacuum Distillation Stage to separate
Wax Distillate as FCC feed. Vacuum Residue  (>509 , >550, >585) medium
Density, high Sulphur. suitable as high Sulphur Fuel Oil or bunker
grade only.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  16.1 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   136.0  deg. C.

Name: Surmont Heavy SHB (INSP) Aug 23
Comments:
Alberta, western Canada. Estimated reserves are 15 billion barrels of
oil, of which at least 5 billion barrels are recoverable bitumen
quality oil. Steam Assisted Gravity Drainage (SAGD) technology is used
to extract bitumen from the oil sands. Steam, generated by a nearby
plant, is injected into the top horizontal well. The injected steam
heats the oil to a temperature where it can flow to the bottom
horizontal producing well. The water and oil form an emulsion that is
then sent to the plant where the water is recycled for making new steam
and the oil is blended with synthetic oil then shipped via pipeline to
the US for refining. Surmont Heavy Blend is a heavy (22.1 degrees ),
high sulfur (3.1 wt percent), acidic (1.58 mg KOH/g) synthetic crude
oil. Production, which began in 2007, averaged 23,000 b/d in 2010.
Conoco Phillips is the operator and holds a 50 percent interest while
Total SA holds the remaining 50 percent interest.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  15.7 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   140.5  deg. C.

Name: SuTuDen Exp Bld (CVX) Jun '10
Comments:
Sutu Den is a blend of crudes from several fields located in the
southeast corner of block 15-1 in the Cuulong Basin of Vietnam. It is
processed and stored in the Thai Binh-VN FPSO, formerly known as the
Cuulong M/V 9. The three main producing fields, also known as the
Golden Triangle, Sutu Den (including Sutu Den Northeast), Sutu Vang,
and Sutu Trang hold an estimated reserve of 600 million boe, 720
million boe, and 120 million boe, respectively. Sutu Den, the main
component, came on line in 2003 and production for Sutu Den Northeast
began in May 2010. Sutu Vang initiated in 2008 and Sutu Trang is
targeted to begin in 2012. Sutu Den is a waxy, light, low sulfur crude
(36 deg API and 0.07 weight percent Sulfur). Production of the Sutu Den
field is in decline because of water pressure issues associated with
fractured basement reservoirs in the Cuu Long Basin, however this is
offset by an increase production of the lighter Sutu Vang (37 deg API)
which is causing an increase in the blend s API. Production rates in
2009 averaged 93,000 b/d and are expected to increase in 2010 and
beyond as Sutu Den Northeast production ramps up and Sutu Trang comes
on line. The fields are operated by the Cuu Long Joint Operating Co., a
joint venture between Petrovietnam (50 percent), ConocoPhillips (23.3
percent), Korea National Oil Corp. (14.2 percent), SK Innovation (9
percent) and Geopetrol (3.5 percent).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  14.5 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   136.8  deg. C.

Name: Synbit SHB (Total) '10
Comments:
The Surmont Oil Sands Project is located about 37 miles southeast of
Fort McMurray in northern Alberta, western Canada. Estimated reserves
are 15 billion barrels of oil, of which at least 5 billion barrels are
recoverable bitumen quality oil. Steam Assisted Gravity Drainage (SAGD)
technology is used to extract bitumen from the oil sands. Steam,
generated by a nearby plant, is injected into the top horizontal well.
The injected steam heats the oil to a temperature where it can flow to
the bottom horizontal producing well. The water and oil form an
emulsion that is then sent to the plant where the water is recycled for
making new steam and the oil is blended with synthetic oil then shipped
via pipeline to the US for refining. Surmont Heavy Blend is a heavy,
high sulfur synthetic crude oil with an API of 19 degrees and 3 weight
percent sulfur. Production began in 2007. In 2010, production averaged
23,000 b/d. Conoco Phillips is the operator and holds a 50 percent
interest while Total SA holds the remaining 50 percent interest.

Name: Syncrude Swt Bld (CCQA)May '10
Comments:
Syncrude Synthetic (SSB), a light (31.8 degree API) gravity sweet (0.17
weight percent sulfur) synthetic crude oil, is produced from the
Syncrude Canada Project. The project, which began producing in 1978,
upgrades bitumen, a black and asphalt like oil, into lighter
hydrocarbon streams, such as naphtha, Light Gas Oil (LGO) and Heavy Gas
Oil (HGO), and blends them to create a light, low sulfur synthetic
crude oil. The bitumen is from the Athabasca Oil Sands Deposit located
north of Fort McMurray, Alberta, Canada. The reserves hold
approximately 1.7 trillion barrels of bitumen and are considered the
largest petroleum resource in the world. With current available
technologies, over 175 billion barrels is recoverable. The project
produces about 350,000 barrels of synthetic crude oil each day.
Syncrude Canada Ltd, a joint venture company comprised of Canadian Oil
Sands Trust (36.74 percent), Sinopec (9.03 percent), Imperial Oil (25
percent), Nippon Oil (5 percent), Murphy Oil Co. Ltd. (5 percent),
Nexen Inc. (7.23 percent), and Petro-Canada (12 percent) owns and
operates the project.

Comments:
2006 Total assay. Syrian light is produced by Syria's state-run Sytrol.
 Historically about half the production was exported.  Production is
ranges  36-38 API with 0.5-0.8% sulfur.  With the need to lighten is
domestic crude slate, more of the barrels may be used in-country.
Loading Ports: are Banias; and Tartous . Its aliases are   Syrian
Export Blend and  Syrian Light.  It is a blend of several fields in
northeastern Syria, mainly in the Deir ez Zour region where commercial
quantities of oil were first discovered in the late 1980s. The primary
contributing fields are al-Thayyem, Omar, Deir ez Zour, Al Isba, Tanak,

Name: TalangDumb-bell Mix (3rd) '08
Comments:
Grid report--calclated assay. COP operation.  Seems this is Talang: In
1921 Nederlandsche Koloniale Petroleum M aatschappij (NKPM), formed by
Standard of New Jersey  (SONJ), discovered the Pendopo/Talang Akar
Field. This discovery in the Talang Akar Formation sandstone is the
largest oil field in South Sumatra with estimated reserves of 360
MMBOE. the largest oil field in Asia is minas.  Pour is low for K
value--a bit low but possible. GC data are inconsistent with yields. Hg
is probably wrong units as reported.  Perhaps ppb not ppm! Acid is 1.8
!  very unusual for this gravity so this might be another input
error-not likely this is a high acid crude but there are other
peculiarities: hi metals, nitrogen (although possible), hi mcr.  There
is an error in the asphaltenes as printed.  My conclusion is that this
is a dumb-bell mixture of unknown components-a very light crude or
condensate and a heavy biodegraded crude.  Most likely, this is a paper
not a physical lab assay.  There are many rice mills in the area and it
is possible rice-based biofuels are added-calculated data based on
crude oil db would not reflect the needed parameters. date of assay is
unknown-- all we know is when the trader printed it. Could not put
unknown so it is left blank. WAX CVX value calculated IRON value
calculated SOLVENT POWER value calculated SOLVENT REQUIREMENT value
calculated

Name: Tantawan (ITS) Apr17 '14
Comments:
Tantawan is a light gravity (41.9 degrees API), low sulfur (0.04 wt
percent) crude oil with a high pour point (63.7 degrees F) and high
mercury concentration (682 ppb). The field is located in Block B8/32 in
the Pattani Basin, Gulf of Thailand, offshore Thailand. Tantawan has
initial reserves of 53 million boe and remaining reserves of 16 million
boe. In 2014, production averaged 2,500 b/d. The Tantawan development
is made up six platforms which include two wellhead platforms (A and B)
with 12 wells each, two nine well platforms (C and D), Platform E and
Platform H. Oil and gas from the field is piped to the Tantawan
Explorer FPSO which can process up to 120 mmcfd of gas and 50,000 b/d
of oil and condensate and can store 1 million boe. Chevron operates the
field and has 51.66 percent ownership. Other participants are MOECO
(16.71 percent), Krisenergy (4.63 percent), PTTEP (25 percent) and
Sophonpanich (2 percent).
*** The GC Analysis Covers  18.7 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   134.4  deg. C.

Name: Tapis Exp Bld (ITS) '12
Comments:
Tapis Export Blend, also known as Pulai and Tapis Blend, is a high
quality, light, sweet benchmark crude with an API of 44.3 degrees and
0.036 wt percent sulfur. It is produced from several fields located
offshore Malaysia in the South China Sea. The producing reservoirs at
Tapis are Miocene Age Group J (Tapis formation 1) sandstones that
contain rim-type oil accumulations with associated gas caps. Tapis
Export Blend is currently composed of the output of 16 fields with
Bekok, Irong, Irong Barat, Kepong, Larut, Palas, Pulai, Seligif,
Seligih, Semangkok, Tabu, Tapis, Tinggi, and Tiong being the major
contributors to the blend. Tapis was first discovered in 1969 and is
now producing 200,000 b/d (2010), approximately one third of Malaysia's
output. Operators Petronas and Exxon have signed a 25 year production
sharing contract that calls for enhanced oil recovery techniques that
is expected to increase output by 2013. Exxon operates 10 fields and
owns 30 percent equity. Petronas operates the other six fields and is
entitled to at least 50 percent of all the crude oil output with other
joint venture partners taking the rest.
*** The GC Analysis Covers  22.9 LV%  of crude up to a TBP of   134.7  deg. C.
